---
import Tabs from "@xoji/astro/Tabs.astro";
import Card from "@xoji/astro/Card.astro";
import Stack from "@xoji/astro/Stack.astro";
import Cluster from "@xoji/astro/Cluster.astro";
import Heading from "@xoji/astro/Heading.astro";
import Text from "@xoji/astro/Text.astro";
import Badge from "@xoji/astro/Badge.astro";
---

<Stack gap={6}>
	<Card>
		<Stack gap={3} slot="header">
			<Heading level={3} size="lg">Live & keyboard-driven</Heading>
			<Text size="sm" tone="muted">
				Click a tab, or focus the tablist and use arrow keys, Home, and End. The panel swaps in place.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Tabs variant="underline" value="derive" label="Engine concepts">
			<button slot="tab" value="derive">Derive</button>
			<button slot="tab" value="cover">Cover</button>
			<button slot="tab" value="emit">Emit</button>
			<div slot="panel">
				<Stack gap={2}>
					<Text weight="semibold">Derivation</Text>
					<Text size="sm" tone="muted">
						An algorithm maps a handful of anchors and knobs into a full,
						internally-consistent register of OKLCH-derived tokens.
					</Text>
				</Stack>
			</div>
			<div slot="panel">
				<Stack gap={2}>
					<Text weight="semibold">Coverage</Text>
					<Text size="sm" tone="muted">
						The only hard contract: every token a component consumes must be
						produced by the active register. The check is live.
					</Text>
				</Stack>
			</div>
			<div slot="panel">
				<Stack gap={2}>
					<Text weight="semibold">Emit</Text>
					<Text size="sm" tone="muted">
						Once derived, a theme is just CSS custom properties plus the
						cascade — emit it as CSS or JSON and you're done.
					</Text>
				</Stack>
			</div>
		</Tabs>
	</Card>

	<Card>
		<Stack gap={3} slot="header">
			<Heading level={3} size="lg">Three variants</Heading>
			<Text size="sm" tone="muted">
				Underline, pill, and enclosed — the same tablist, three different framings.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Stack gap={5}>
			<Stack gap={2}>
				<Text as="span" size="xs" tone="subtle" mono>variant="underline"</Text>
				<Tabs variant="underline" label="Underline tabs">
					<button slot="tab" value="a">Overview</button>
					<button slot="tab" value="b">Pricing</button>
					<button slot="tab" value="c">Reviews</button>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">The default — a quiet underline marks the selected tab.</Text></div>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Pricing panel content.</Text></div>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Reviews panel content.</Text></div>
				</Tabs>
			</Stack>

			<Stack gap={2}>
				<Text as="span" size="xs" tone="subtle" mono>variant="pill"</Text>
				<Tabs variant="pill" label="Pill tabs">
					<button slot="tab" value="a">Overview</button>
					<button slot="tab" value="b">Pricing</button>
					<button slot="tab" value="c">Reviews</button>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">A filled pill carries the selection.</Text></div>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Pricing panel content.</Text></div>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Reviews panel content.</Text></div>
				</Tabs>
			</Stack>

			<Stack gap={2}>
				<Text as="span" size="xs" tone="subtle" mono>variant="enclosed"</Text>
				<Tabs variant="enclosed" label="Enclosed tabs">
					<button slot="tab" value="a">Overview</button>
					<button slot="tab" value="b">Pricing</button>
					<button slot="tab" value="c">Reviews</button>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Folder-style tabs that connect to the panel.</Text></div>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Pricing panel content.</Text></div>
					<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Reviews panel content.</Text></div>
				</Tabs>
			</Stack>
		</Stack>
	</Card>

	<Card>
		<Stack gap={3} slot="header">
			<Heading level={3} size="lg">Headless tablist</Heading>
			<Text size="sm" tone="muted">
				With no panels, Tabs is a bare tablist driving a value. The main view swaps on
				`change`, while the sidebar lives outside the tabs and keeps its own state across switches.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<div class="headless-demo">
			<Tabs tablist variant="pill" value="editor" label="Workspace view" id="headless-tabs">
				<button slot="tab" value="editor">Editor</button>
				<button slot="tab" value="preview">Preview</button>
				<button slot="tab" value="diff">Diff</button>
			</Tabs>
			<div class="headless-demo__body">
				<main class="headless-demo__main">
					<div data-view="editor"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">The editor view: code lives here.</Text></div>
					<div data-view="preview" hidden><Text size="sm" tone="muted">The preview view: rendered output.</Text></div>
					<div data-view="diff" hidden><Text size="sm" tone="muted">The diff view: what changed.</Text></div>
				</main>
				<aside class="headless-demo__aside">
					<Text as="span" size="xs" tone="subtle" weight="semibold">Inspector (persists)</Text>
					<input class="headless-demo__note" type="text" placeholder="Type here, switch tabs, come back" aria-label="Persistent note" />
				</aside>
			</div>
		</div>
		<script is:inline>
			(() => {
				const tabs = document.getElementById("headless-tabs");
				const views = document.querySelectorAll(".headless-demo__main [data-view]");
				tabs?.addEventListener("change", (e) => {
					const value = e.detail.value;
					views.forEach((v) => (v.hidden = v.getAttribute("data-view") !== value));
				});
			})();
		</script>
	</Card>

	<Card>
		<Stack gap={3} slot="header">
			<Cluster gap={2} align="center" justify="between">
				<Heading level={3} size="lg">Sizes & disabled state</Heading>
				<Badge tone="info">size="sm"</Badge>
			</Cluster>
			<Text size="sm" tone="muted">
				The compact size, with a disabled tab that's skipped by keyboard navigation.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Tabs variant="pill" size="sm" value="active" label="Account settings">
			<button slot="tab" value="active">Profile</button>
			<button slot="tab" value="security">Security</button>
			<button slot="tab" value="billing" disabled>Billing</button>
			<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Edit your display name and avatar.</Text></div>
			<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Manage passwords and two-factor auth.</Text></div>
			<div slot="panel"><Text size="sm" tone="muted">Billing is disabled on this plan.</Text></div>
		</Tabs>
	</Card>
</Stack>

<style>
	.headless-demo {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-4);
	}
	.headless-demo__body {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: var(--space-4);
	}
	@media (min-width: 40rem) {
		.headless-demo__body {
			grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 2fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
		}
	}
	.headless-demo__main {
		padding: var(--space-4);
		background: var(--bg-2);
		border-radius: var(--radius-md);
		min-height: 4rem;
	}
	.headless-demo__aside {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-2);
		padding: var(--space-4);
		border: var(--border-thin) solid var(--line);
		border-radius: var(--radius-md);
	}
	.headless-demo__note {
		font: inherit;
		padding: var(--space-2);
		color: var(--fg-1);
		background: var(--bg-1);
		border: var(--border-thin) solid var(--line);
		border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
	}
</style>
